HEADWORD: Silico-
<hw>Sil"i*co-</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>. <fld>(Chem.)</fld> <def>A combining
form (also used adjectively) denoting <xex>the presence of silicon</xex>
or <xex>its compounds</xex>; <as>as, <ex>silico</ex>benzoic,
<ex>silico</ex>fluoride, etc.</as></def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Silicofluoric</ent>⟦br⟧
